<section>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Grid</h1>
        <hr>
        <p class="lead">We&rsquo;re using a complex folding compound grid for maximum flexibility in our responsive layouts. This is a fluid grid with flexible columns and fixed-width gutters to maintain proportional spacing and alignment for all screen dimensions.</p>

        <p>Our grid system is not attached to classes like other pre-packaged CSS grid systems. Instead, they are set in SCSS using our simple grid varables. This keeps our markup clean and our layout much easier to modify at various breakpoints.</p>
        <p><em>E.G. To specify a width of four columns of a six column grid ($c6 == 1 column of a 6-column grid), use the following:</em></p>

        <div class="code-block">
            <ol class="line-numbers">
                <li><code>.object{</code></li>
                <li><code>  <span class="code__comment">/* Use any of the following mixins to set box-sizing & gutters. */</span></code></li>
                <li><code>  <span class="code__comment">// @include box; /* Sets box-sizing to border-box. */</span></code></li>
                <li><code>  <span class="code__comment">// @include gutters; /* Applies gutter spacing to sides of object. */</span></code></li>
                <li><code>  @include wrap; <span class="code__comment">/* OR wrap sets both box & gutters in one mixin. */</span></code></li>
                <li><code>    width:$c6*4; <span class="code__comment">/* $c6 = 1 column of a 6-column grid. Mulitply by 4 to specify 4 columns wide. */</span></code></li>
                <li><code>    margin-left:$c6*1; <span class="code__comment">/* Moves object 1 column to the right. */</span></code></li>
                <li><code>}</code></li>
            </ol>
      </div>

    </div>
</section>
